<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Border-width applied to element with display list-item</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/box.html#propdef-border-width" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/box.html#border-width-properties" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The 'border-width' property applies to elements with a display of list-item." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                border-style: solid;
                border-width: 1in;
                display: list-item;
                height: 1in;
                margin-left: 2em;
                width: 1in;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is a marker bullet on the left-hand side of box below and all four sides are the same width. (Note: this will make a large square surrounding a smaller white square.)</p>
        <div></div>
    </body>
</html>